# Sofrito de Verduras

Prep Time: 15 min

Cook Time: 55 min

Serves: 4

## Ingredients

- 1 large aubergine, diced into 1cm cubes
- 4 large vine tomatoes, grated (or 1x 400g tin plum tomatoes)
- 1 large white onion, finely diced
- 1 red bell pepper, finely diced
- 3 garlic cloves, minced
- 4 tbsp extra virgin olive oil
- 1 tsp smoked paprika
- ½ tsp dried oregano
- 1 tbsp sherry vinegar
- sea salt and black pepper
- 4 seabass fillets
- 4 large eggs
- 500 g new potatoes

## Method

- Toss the diced aubergine in a pinch of sea salt and let it sit for 15 minutes to draw out moisture, then pat dry.
- Heat half of the olive oil in a pan and gently fry the onion and red pepper for 15 minutes until incredibly soft and sweet.
- Add the garlic, the remaining olive oil, and the aubergine, and fry for 10 minutes until the aubergine is tender.
- Stir in the smoked paprika and oregano for 30 seconds, then pour in the sherry vinegar to deglaze the pan.
- Add the tomatoes and seasoning, and simmer on low for 30 minutes until thick, jammy, and the oil just begins to separate.

Served with smashed new potatoes, a poached egg and seabass
